---
import Section from '../section.astro';
---

<Section id="positioning" data-section="positioning" className="py-24">
  <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-5xl overflow-hidden rounded-[2.5rem] border border-[#EAEAEA] bg-white px-8 py-16 text-center shadow-[0_8px_30px_rgb(0,0,0,0.08)] md:px-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-4xl space-y-8">
      <h2 class="text-balance text-3xl font-bold md:text-5xl lg:leading-[1.15] text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-[#111111] to-[#777777]">
        Dev shops build what you spec. <br class="hidden md:block" />
        We build what your users will pay for.
      </h2>
      <p class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-balance text-lg text-[#666666] md:text-xl md:leading-relaxed">
        A dev shop takes your requirements, disappears for months and hands back code. If the spec was wrong, that's your problem. We work as your <span class="text-[#111111] font-semibold">in-house product team</span>. We pressure test the idea, cut the features that don't matter and get a real product in front of real users fast. Because the goal isn't shipping code. The goal is your first 100 paying users.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Section>
